## Organization Overview

- **Full name**: Northbound Treatment Services®
- **Type**: Private behavioral healthcare — addiction treatment & dual-diagnosis (co-occurring mental health)
- **Founded**: 1988 as National Therapeutic Services (NTS)
- **Rebranded**: 2008, acquired by Paul Alexander; renamed Northbound Treatment Services
- **Years in operation**: 38+ (as of 2026)
- **Staff size**: 51–200 employees
- **Core philosophy**: Addiction is a primary, progressive, chronic brain disease — not a moral failing. Trauma-informed, root-cause treatment.
- **Mantra**: "Our client's best interest is our best interest."
- **Guiding principles**: Clinical Innovation · Service Excellence · Organizational Health

