## Full Continuum of Care

1. **Medically Supervised Detox** — Sub-acute residential at Garden Grove; IMS certified; MAT available; 24/7 medical monitoring
2. **Residential Treatment** — Co-ed clinical programming at Garden Grove (The Grove); gender-specific residential wings; campus-style setting; individualized plans; immersive (separate men's/women's residential pages are not published)
3. **Partial Hospitalization (PHP)** — Structured daytime programming at Newport Beach; transitional step-down from Garden Grove residential
4. **Virtual IOP (HomeBound)** — Online intensive outpatient for California residents; no in-person IOP or standalone sober living
5. **Aftercare & Alumni** — Lifelong support, events, relapse-prevention resources

---

## Specialized Programs (Ownable Differentiators)

- **InVivo® Model** — Clients practice real-world skills, stresses, and independence *during* treatment to build self-efficacy and ease the transition back to daily life
- **Collegebound®** — Residential-only specialized track at Garden Grove for young adults maintaining or resuming academic progress during residential treatment
- **Careerbound®** — Residential-only career reintegration and professional development track at Garden Grove
- **Spiritual Track** — Holistic track at Garden Grove (sound therapy, breathwork, meditation, somatic yoga); integrated into residential and PHP; distinct from faith-based LINKS
- **Wolf Assisted Therapy** — Unique experiential program
- **Adventure Therapy** — Outdoor/adventure-based healing
- **Faith-Based Recovery (Christ-Centered)** — Spiritually integrated program
- **Family Services** — Structured family therapy, education workshops, ongoing communication
- **Alumni Program** — Ongoing events, activities, lifelong community, relapse-prevention support

(Published pages only — no standalone Veterans Track, Music Recovery, in-person IOP, sober living, or Wahler Scholarship pages.)

