## Tone & Messaging Guidelines

- Compassionate, direct, never clinical to the point of being cold
- Lead with hope — recovery is possible, attainable, and supported
- Use first-person warmth: "we," "our team," "your journey"
- Validate difficulty without catastrophizing
- Anchor every claim in a specific metric, accreditation, or verifiable differentiator
- Avoid vague superlatives ("world-class", "best", "top") unless backed by a specific award or credential (e.g. Dr. Sanchez's "Best of Newport Beach" recognition)
- Always note insurance coverage and that benefits verification is free
- DHCS license number (#300661CP) can be cited wherever trust signals are needed

